      <guid>https://elias.fish/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;hello&#34;&gt;Hello!&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div style=&#34;float: right; text-align: center; margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;https://elias.fish/images/-aura.jpg&#34; style=&#34;max-width: 200px; display: block;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;small&gt;😎&lt;/small&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m Elias and I&amp;rsquo;m currently finishing my last year at The Game Assembly. I always wanted to make my own games when I was younger so I spent a lot of time making art both sprites and animations, neither very good. After I confidently concluded I knew everything about making game art I chose a high school program specializing in game programming. During the program I realized I was no artist at all but luckily discovered that I really liked programming!&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://elias.fish/CV.pdf&#34;&gt;View CV&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
